Comment: 0,0:39:59.46,0:40:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The Zentradi are now speaking Japanese with occasional words left in Zentran, therefore I left these lines in yellow (to match other lines spoken in Japanese) instead of the white that was previously used for lines spoken fully in Zentran. The recording script usually shows the entire line in Japanese without any foreign words, so this is what I used for the subtitle script, but I put the Zentran pronunciation in furigana above the respective words, similar to how furigana is sometimes used in Japanese subtitles to show pronunciations of English words with the Japanese meaning. They also pronounce words like キス and 抱く with elongated vowels as shown in some Japanese transcripts found on the internet, but this isn't shown in the recording script so I decided not to show it in the captions.  I did use kagikakko when the Zentraedi say 抱く and キス, this wasn't in the recording script but was used in Super Robot Taisen Alpha.
